==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /'mεʒə/
*[[SAMPA]]: /"mEZU@/

====Hyphenation====
mea&middot;sure

===Etymology===
Of Middle English origin, from French '''[[mesure]]''', from Latin noun '''[[mensura]]'''

===Noun===
'''measure''', plural '''[[measures]]'''

#the [[quantity]], [[size]], [[weight]], [[distance]] or [[capacity]] of a [[substance]] compared to a designated [[standard]]
#the precise designated distance between two objects or points
#the act of [[measuring]]
#a musical designation consisting of all notes and or rests delineated by two vertical bars; an equal and regular division of the whole of a composition
#a [[rule]], [[ruler]] or [[measuring stick]]
#a [[tactic]], [[strategy]] or piece of [[legislation]]

===Verb===
'''measure''', third person singular '''[[measures]]''', past and past participle '''[[measured]]''', present participle '''[[measuring]]'''

=====''transitive''=====
# ascertain the quantity of a unit of material via calculated comparison with respect to a standard.
# estimate the unit size of something
# obtain or set apart; to mark in even increments

